p: Carvacrol as a major phytocompound in OEO may be responsible, in part, for the antiproliferative potential of OEO, as indicated by others, acting as suppressor of kinase ERK1/2 (extracellular signal-regulated protein kinase1/2) and AKT (Protein kinase B) proteins while upregulating BAX and phosphor c-Jun N-terminal kinase ( p-JNK) protein expression [ 18].
